Samsung has announced that its Galaxy S10 5G smartphone will launch on 5 April 2019 in Korea. The device is based on the Samsung Galaxy S10 which launched earlier this year, but features 5G connectivity and a bigger 6.7-inch display. “We are at the beginning of a new era where the incredible speed and connectivity of 5G becomes a reality, bringing the world closer to Samsung’s vision of connected living,” said DJ Koh, CEO of Samsung Electronics. “With speeds up to roughly 20-times faster than 4G networks, consumers on a 5G network can download a full season of a TV show in minutes.” To handle the increased demands of the larger screen and 5G connectivity, Samsung has fitted the S10 5G with a 4,500mAh battery. Following the announcement, TechRadar has reported pricing for the Galaxy S10 5G. The device is priced as follows in Korea: For comparison purposes, the Galaxy S10 and S10+ are priced as follows in Korea. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-301448" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-1.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="539" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-1.jpg 700w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-1-475x400.jpg 475w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-1-510x430.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter wp-image-301452" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="539" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G.jpg 700w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-475x400.jpg 475w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/S10-5G-510x430.jpg 510w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />